      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZERO KILLER (1) missed the frame and safely held latest finishing 6th at Bendigo following on from a win (22.34) at this track the start prior. Solid record here at the distance winning three races. Tough to beat if on-song. GAPING MARGIN (2) was a big winner two back scoring by 1.5 lengths then got further back last time but came home hard into third and beaten 6 lengths at this track (22.52). Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to her name from five starts. Hard to beat again. LAKEVIEW MITCH (7) finished second (22.19) two back at Ballarat but out of the placings last time when 6th at Shepparton. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and three minor placings to his credit. Worth another chance. ASTON CLEESE (8) missed the placings here most recently but can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
